# Moss Quilt Cursor Rules

## Context files
- [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md)
- [DECISIONS.md](mdc:DECISIONS.md)
- [cursorrules](mdc:cursorrules)

## Before making changes
- Read [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) for current project context
- Show a plan before executing anything major
- Ask about tradeoffs when multiple approaches exist
- Wait for approval before big structural changes

## After completing work
- Update [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) with what changed and why
- Mark completed items with ✅ in the “What’s Built” section
- Note any new patterns or decisions made

## Action over explanation
- If you can execute an action directly via tools, do it immediately
- Only give manual instructions when you literally cannot perform the action

## Autonomous error resolution
- Read errors/logs, identify root cause, implement fix, test
- Iterate up to 3 times before asking for help

## Design rules — never break these
- Font: Neue Haas Grotesk Text Pro 55 everywhere, no exceptions
- Primary color: #B8E600
- Quilt piece outlines: 0.5px black only
- Layout: truly edge to edge, no page margins
- Grain texture: medium, with 10% yellow-green tint overlay on entire page
- All photos fill their piece using object-fit: cover
- Header always floats over quilt with no background, 20px padding, black text

## Code quality
- Prefer simplicity over cleverness
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Keep Supabase piece labels consistent: block-[number]-piece-[number]

## Anti-patterns to avoid
- Don’t add authentication yet
- Don’t add photo moderation yet
- Don’t use React/Next.js; keep it simple HTML/CSS/JS
- Don’t add animations beyond upload hover arrow + mobile pulse
- Don’t add a header background
- Don’t over-engineer for scale we don’t have yet
